    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-04-28T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-04-28T11:00:00-05:00" n="256"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/2613: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cole</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-28T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >April 28, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received April 28—2:46 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>177. Following received from General Weygand: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The General wishes to express his sincere thanks to the United States
                            Government for its communication contained in your 98, April 24, and to
                            express hope that [it?] will be possible carry out agreement covering
                            ‘commercial exchanges’ under the terms approved by the United States
                            Government.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
